<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="02986652-f5bd-4663-873a-664f34ed2444" >

    <h2>About Crystal</h2> 
<p>Crystal is an equity educator and a community engagement and development specialist with over fifteen years of experience in the non-profit sector. Crystal is also an experienced anti-racist writer, speaker and facilitator on human rights and community issues. A first generation Canadian born to Caribbean immigrants, Crystal connects her equity work to the continued struggle for racialized and marginalized groups as an extension of her ancestral teachings and legacy work.</p> 
<p>In her role as the Education and Awareness Consultant, Crystal creates and facilitates workshops and consults with community members to raise their awareness on equity, diversity and inclusion-related topics. Crystal enjoys that moment when equity education ‘clicks’ for learners and something new is shared to bring people together across shared space.</p> 
<p>Crystal is a passionate leader working towards ensuring the inclusion of all people into the rich tapestry of the university. She is skilled at creating empathetic working relationships and meeting learners where they are in their equity journey. Her approach to coaching enables learners to engage in new and challenging topics while empowering them to navigate “brave spaces” with others.</p>
    





